message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Zimbabwe in the past 5 years was the ousting of long-time President Robert Mugabe in November 2017. After ruling the country for 37 years, Mugabe was removed from power through a military intervention and pressure from the public. This event marked a major turning point in Zimbabwe's history and led to the inauguration of Emmerson Mnangagwa as the new president.
